achments=None, long_term_memory='Scrolled down the page by 15.0 pages (requested: 15.0, 632px per page)', extracted_content='🔍 Scrolled down the page by 15.0 pages (requested: 15.0, 632px per page)', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory="<url>\nhttps://science.nasa.gov/\n</url>\n<query>\nProvide a complete list of all NASA science missions displayed on this page, including each mission's title and a brief description.\n</query>\n<result>\nIMAP – Launched September\u202f24\u202f2025; will help researchers better understand the boundary of the heliosphere, the huge bubble created by the Sun that surrounds and protects our solar system.  \n\nTRACERS – Launched July\u202f23\u202f2025; will study magnetic reconnection—when solar activity disrupts Earth’s magnetic field—to improve understanding and preparedness for space‑weather effects.  \n\nLucy – Captured detailed images of asteroid Donaldjohanson during an April\u202f20\u202f2025 fly‑by; the spacecraft is now traveling toward the distant Trojan asteroids.\n</result>", extracted_content="<url>\nhttps://science.nasa.gov/\n</url>\n<query>\nProvide a complete list of all NASA science missions displayed on this page, including each mission's title and a brief description.\n</query>\n<result>\nIMAP – Launched September\u202f24\u202f2025; will help researchers better understand the boundary of the heliosphere, the huge bubble created by the Sun that surrounds and protects our solar system.  \n\nTRACERS – Launched July\u202f23\u202f2025; will study magnetic reconnection—when solar activity disrupts Earth’s magnetic field—to improve understanding and preparedness for space‑weather effects.  \n\nLucy – Captured detailed images of asteroid Donaldjohanson during an April\u202f20\u202f2025 fly‑by; the spacecraft is now traveling toward the distant Trojan asteroids.\n</result>", include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory=None, extracted_content='Clicked element', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'click_x': 170.0, 'click_y': 0, 'new_tab_opened': False}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory=None, extracted_content='Clicked element', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'click_x': 170.0, 'click_y': 315.6328125, 'new_tab_opened': False}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory=None, extracted_content='Clicked element', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'click_x': 1107.3671875, 'click_y': 631, 'new_tab_opened': False}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory=None, extracted_content='Clicked element', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata={'click_x': 1107.3671875, 'click_y': 315.96875, 'new_tab_opened': False}, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory='Scrolled down the page by 5.0 pages (requested: 5.0, 632px per page)', extracted_content='🔍 Scrolled down the page by 5.0 pages (requested: 5.0, 632px per page)', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory="Extracted content from https://science.nasa.gov/science-missions/ for query: Provide a complete list of all NASA science missions displayed on this page, including each mission's title and a brief description.\nContent saved to file system: Extracted content saved to file extracted_content_4.md successfully. and displayed in <read_state>.", extracted_content="<url>\nhttps://science.nasa.gov/science-missions/\n</url>\n<query>\nProvide a complete list of all NASA science missions displayed on this page, including each mission's title and a brief description.\n</query>\n<result>\nIMAP – Launched September\u202f24\u202f2025; will help researchers better understand the boundary of the heliosphere, a huge bubble created by the Sun surrounding and protecting our solar system.  \nTRACERS – Launched July\u202f23\u202f2025; will study magnetic reconnection—when solar activity disrupts Earth’s magnetic field—to help scientists better understand and prepare for the effects of space weather.  \nLucy – Captured stunning, detailed images of asteroid Donaldjohanson during a fly‑by on April\u202f20\u202f2025 as the spacecraft heads toward the distant Trojan asteroids.  \n\n3D Tissue Chips – Developing tissue chips that can be used for modeling of acute and/or chronic exposures for\u202f6\u202fmonths or longer.  \nA‑Train: The Afternoon Constellation – Describes the A‑Train, a constellation of Earth‑observing satellites positioned high above Earth’s surface.  \nAble\u202f1 (Pioneer\u202f0) – First‑ever launch to the Moon and humanity’s first attempt to reach it.  \nAble\u202f2 (Pioneer\u202f1) – Lunar mission jointly managed by the U.S. Air Force and NASA.  \nAble\u202f4B (Pioneer\u202fP‑3) – Part of a U.S. push to reach the Moon after earlier attempts.  \nAble\u202f5A (Pioneer\u202fP‑30) – U.S. probe with a mission similar to its failed predecessor, Able\u202f4B.  \nAble\u202f5B (Pioneer\u202fP‑31) – U.S. spacecraft launched to orbit the Moon after two unsuccessful predecessors.  \nACE – NASA’s Advanced Composition Explorer collects and analyzes particles of solar, interplanetary, interstellar, and galactic origins.  \nACME – Advances combustion technology via fundamental microgravity experiments to improve efficiency and reduce emissions in terrestrial combustion.  \nACRIMSAT – The Active Cavity Irradiance Monitor Satellite spent 14\u202fyears in orbit monitoring Earth’s main energy source, radiation.  \nACT‑America – *(description not provided)*  \nADEOS\u202f/\u202fMidori – *(description not provided)*  \nAdvanced Plant Habitat – Conducts plant bioscience research aboard the International Space Station; the largest, fully automated plant facility in space.  \nAIM – *(description not provided)*  \nAirMOSS – *(description not provided)*  \nAkatsuki – Venus orbiter launched 21\u202fMay\u202f2010 from Tanegashima, Japan; currently successful and in progress.  \nApollo\u202f15 Subsatellite – Launched 4\u202fAug\u202f1971 from Cape Canaveral; orbited Earth’s Moon.  \nApollo\u202f16 Subsatellite – Launched 24\u202fApr\u202f1972 from Cape Canaveral; orbited Earth’s Moon.  \nAqua – Earth‑orbiting satellite (Earth Orbiter).  \nAquarius – Joint U.S./Argentinian Aquarius/SAC‑D mission launched 10\u202fJun\u202f2011 to study ocean salinity; mission ended.  \nArcstone – First mission dedicated exclusively to measuring moonlight (lunar reflectance) from space.  \nARCTAS – *(description not provided)*  \nASCA – *(description not provided)*  \nASTHROS – *(description not provided)*  \nAstro Observatory\u202f1 – *(description not provided)*  \nAstro Observatory\u202f2 – *(description not provided)*  \nAthena\u202fEPIC – SmallSat mission coordinated by NASA, U.S. Space Force, NOAA, and NovaWurks to gather scientific data.  \nATLAS – Atlas program; ATLAS‑1 was the first of the series of Shuttle flights, an important part of the long‑term program.  \nAtmospheric Remote‑sensing Infrared Exoplanet Large‑survey – *(description not provided)*  \nAtmospheric Tomography Mission (ATom) – *(description not provided)*  \nATS – Applications Technology Satellite series conceived as a follow‑on to earlier experimental satellites.  \nATTREX – *(description not provided)*  \nAura – Earth‑orbiting satellite (Earth Orbiter).  \nAWE – Atmospheric Waves Experiment attached to the exterior of the International Space Station to study atmospheric waves.  \nBARREL – Balloon‑based mission to study X‑rays in Earth’s atmosphere near the North and South poles.  \nBBXRT – *(description not provided)*  \nBECCAL – *(description not provided)*  \nBepiColombo – International mission of two spacecraft traveling together to Mercury to orbit the planet.  \nBeresheet – Israel’s first lunar mission and the first private‑company attempt to land on the Moon.  \nBioExpt‑01 – Biological Experiment‑01 on Artemis\u202fI studying how life responds to conditions beyond low Earth orbit.  \nBion\u202f/\u202fBiocosmos – *(description not provided)*  \nBRIC‑24 – *(description not provided)*  \nBurstCube – Shoebox‑sized satellite designed to study the universe’s most powerful explosions.  \nCALIPSO – Earth‑orbiting satellite (Earth Orbiter).  \nCarruthers Geocorona Observatory – Mission to study Earth’s exosphere, the outermost layer of Earth’s atmosphere.  \nCARVE – *(description not provided)*  \nCassini‑Huygens – Saturn orbiter.  \nCATS – *(description not provided)*  \nCeREs – *(description not provided)*  \nCGRO – *(description not provided)*  \nCHAMP – *(description not provided)*\n</result>", include_extracted_content_only_once=True, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory='Scrolled down the page by 5.0 pages (requested: 5.0, 632px per page)', extracted_content='🔍 Scrolled down the page by 5.0 pages (requested: 5.0, 632px per page)', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory='Scrolled down the page by 10.0 pages (requested: 10.0, 632px per page)', extracted_content='🔍 Scrolled down the page by 10.0 pages (requested: 10.0, 632px per page)', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False), ActionResult(is_done=False, success=None, error=None, attachments=None, long_term_memory="<url>\nhttps://www.youtube